# Environment Variables Configuration

This project requires the following environment variables to be set:

## Required Environment Variables

### Supabase Configuration
```
SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-project-url
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key
```

### Retell AI Configuration
```
RETELL_API_KEY=your-retell-api-key
RETELL_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-retell-webhook-secret
```

### Stripe Configuration (Optional)
```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your-stripe-secret-key
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-stripe-webhook-secret
STRIPE_PORTAL_RETURN_URL=https://your-domain.com/billing
```

### Application Configuration
```
VITE_SUPERADMINS_EMAILS=admin@example.com,admin2@example.com
VITE_RUN_TEST_LEVEL=off
VITE_TEST_ORG_ID=
VITE_DISABLE_EMAIL_DELIVERY_FOR_TESTS=true
VITE_ANALYTICS_EXCLUDE_ORGS=[]
```

### Sentry Configuration (Optional)
```
# Set to 'true' to enable Sentry error tracking
VITE_ENABLE_SENTRY=false

# Sentry DSN for error reporting
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=

# Environment name for Sentry (development, staging, production)
VITE_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development

# Repository name for release tracking (e.g., "myorg/myapp")
VITE_REPO_NAME=

# Sentry build-time configuration (for CI)
SENTRY_ORG=
SENTRY_PROJECT=
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=
```

### Optional Configuration
```
VOICE_DEBUG_KEY=your-debug-key-for-voice-demo
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.com,https://your-staging.com
```

## Development Setup

1. Copy this file to `.env` in your project root
2. Fill in the required values
3. Ensure all secrets are properly configured in your deployment environment

## Security Notes

- Never commit actual environment variable values to version control
- Use different keys for development, staging, and production environments
- Rotate API keys and secrets regularly
- Ensure webhook secrets are strong and randomly generated